"title": "8757: folly, effects of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8757: folly, effects of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The attitude that leads to a closing of the mind towards God and his truth, and a false self-confidence, which results in being easily led astray, failure to see danger, unpreparedness and ultimate ruin.</p>\n<h2>Folly gives a false basis for confidence</h2>\n<h3>Contempt for God's wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:7\">PRO 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job28:28\">JOB 28:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:1\">PSA 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps85:8\">PSA 85:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:10\">PSA 111:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:20-Prov1:27\">PRO 1:20–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:1\">PRO 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:2\">PRO 18:2</a></p>\n<h3>Blindness to God's truth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:17\">EPH 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:6\">PSA 92:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:1-Eccl5:4\">ECC 5:1–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:4\">JER 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:39-Luke11:40\">LUK 11:39–11:40</a> <em>hypocrisy in worship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:21\">ROM 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:36\">1CO 15:36</a> <em>failure to understand the nature of death and resurrection</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:23\">2TI 2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:9\">TIT 3:9</a> <em>futile controversies</em></p>\n<h3>Rebellion against God's authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:17\">PSA 107:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:21-Jer5:25\">JER 5:21–5:25</a></p>\n<h3>Self-reliance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:26\">PRO 28:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:28\">PRO 11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:15\">PRO 12:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:12\">PRO 14:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:20\">LUK 12:20</a></p>\n<h2>Folly cannot be hidden</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl10:3\">ECC 10:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:5\">PSA 69:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:23\">PRO 12:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:16\">PRO 13:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:2\">PRO 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:9\">2TI 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Folly opens the way to deception</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:8\">PRO 14:8</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Being led astray</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:15\">PRO 14:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:7-Prov7:23\">PRO 7:7–7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov9:13-Prov9:18\">PRO 9:13–9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:26\">ECC 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:11\">HOS 7:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:1\">GAL 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>Failing to see danger</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:3\">PRO 22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:13\">ECC 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>Being unprepared</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:10\">MAT 25:10</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The consequences of folly</h2>\n<h3>Destruction and ruin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:32\">PRO 1:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:23\">PRO 5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:8\">PRO 10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:17\">ECC 7:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9\">1TI 6:9</a></p>\n<h3>Shame</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:35\">PRO 3:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:13\">PRO 18:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:9\">ISA 44:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:9\">JER 8:9</a></p>\n<h3>Grief to parents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:25\">PRO 17:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:1\">PRO 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:20\">PRO 15:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:21\">PRO 17:21</a></p>\n<h3>Punishment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:22\">PRO 16:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:5\">PSA 38:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:6\">PRO 18:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:3\">PRO 26:3</a></p>\n<h3>Exclusion from God's way of salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:8\">ISA 35:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:10-Matt25:12\">MAT 25:10–25:12</a></p>\n<h2>Folly is persistent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:22\">PRO 27:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:14\">PRO 15:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:11\">PRO 26:11</a></p>\n<h2>Remedies for folly</h2>\n<h3>The forgiveness of foolish actions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:11\">NUM 12:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:8\">JOB 42:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps85:8\">PSA 85:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3-Titus3:5\">TIT 3:3–3:5</a></p>\n<h3>Discipline</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:25\">PRO 19:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:11\">PRO 21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:15\">PRO 22:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:15\">PRO 29:15</a></p>\n<h3>Wisdom and instruction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:5\">PRO 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov14:33\">PRO 14:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:24\">ISA 29:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:20\">ROM 2:20</a></p>",
